---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat – Bring ideas to life">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="app-container">
      <div>
        <p class="section-eyebrow">A calm home for product ideas</p>
        <h1 class="page-hero-title">
          Bring product ideas to life
        </h1>
        <p class="page-hero-subtitle">
          without drowning in tools, feeds, or settings.
        </p>
        <p class="body-text" style="max-width: 640px;">
          Palchat is a small, quiet site for thinking about how you build: short essays, simple mental models, and tiny
          tools you can use in the browser. This is a random experimental site, not a finished product.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="section-tight" style="padding-top: var(--sp-5); padding-bottom: 0;">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="#essay" class="btn btn-primary">
            Read the featured idea
            <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/about" class="btn btn-secondary">
            Learn what Palchat is
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-tight" style="padding-top: 0;">
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="body-text-small section-eyebrow" style="margin: 0;">Format</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">Short essays &amp; simple tools.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="body-text-small section-eyebrow" style="margin: 0;">Noise</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">No logins, no feeds, no notifications.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="body-text-small section-eyebrow" style="margin: 0;">Audience</p>
            <p class="body-text-small">Solo builders, indie hackers, and small teams.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="essay" class="section">
    <div class="app-container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Featured idea</p>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: var(--sp-2);">
          A dependency trap dressed up as efficiency
        </h2>

        <p class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          Using AI and SaaS tools instead of people feels smart. You save money, you move faster, and you can serve more
          customers. The $1k vs $40k slide is easy to show in a deck.
        </p>
        <p class="body-text">
          But there is a quieter cost that does not show up on any invoice: the slow loss of understanding, custody, and
          resilience inside your own work.
        </p>

        <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          <h3 class="section-title" style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: var(--sp-2);">
            What you quietly trade away
          </h3>
          <ul class="body-text">
            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-1);">
              <span style="font-weight: 600;">Understanding</span> — work moves into a black box that you can no longer
              explain.
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--sp-1);">
              <span style="font-weight: 600;">Custody</span> — your data and logic live inside rented systems, not in
              your hands.
            </li>
            <li>
              <span style="font-weight: 600;">Resilience</span> — when a tool changes or disappears, you may lose the
              memory of how your business runs.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <p class="body-text" style="margin-top: var(--sp-3);">
          The point is not to avoid tools. It is to remember that every dependency has a cost, whether or not it shows
          up on the invoice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
